    "narrative": "Today\u2019s slate for LawDog centers on exploiting high-ceiling matchups against soft-throwing rotations. Our strongest play is **Daulton Varsho** (72.31), who benefits from a favorable matchup against Bradley and a massive boost from his current position in the #2 hole, providing him the best opportunity to accumulate counting stats. Following closely is **Bryson Stott** (68.66), whose dynamic platoon advantage and favorable park factors make him a high-floor anchor for the middle infield. We are also leaning heavily on **Taylor Ward** and **Brendan Donovan**, both of whom are projected as \"Strong\" plays (67.73 and 66.36, respectively) due to excellent park factors and favorable matchups against the Bolton and Houser rotations, which are ripe for exploitation.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involved **Gleyber Torres** (53.98), who sat just on the outside of our active lineup. While **Gleyber Torres** carries respectable baseline power, the optimizer ultimately pivoted to **Jonathan Aranda** and **Tyler Freeman** to maintain better category balance. Despite the consistent output from **Gleyber Torres**, he simply lacked the specific matchup ceiling required to displace the high-efficiency volume we expect from the rest of the infield today. We also note that **Yainer Diaz** (37.73) fell well below our 40-point \"Below Floor\" threshold, largely due to a tough draw against a high-tier arm in Gilbert, necessitating his benching to preserve our game caps.\n\nRisks remain focused on the environment and specific high-skill arms. **Tyler Freeman** (54.70) remains in the lineup despite a 39% rain risk; his utility is currently holding steady, but we are monitoring the radar closely. Additionally, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (54.70) presents a potential trap, as his base projection is mitigated significantly by a cold-water matchup against a sub-3.00 xERA arm in Sale. While we are starting **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** for his pedigree, the -19% SP skill penalty reflects the genuine difficulty of today's encounter. Finally, please ensure **Will Smith** remains benched as he is confirmed out of the lineup, ensuring we do not burn unnecessary game slots on a non-participant.",
